Name Rascal/Expressions/Values/Map/getOneFrom
Synopsis Get a random key from a map.
Function &K getOneFrom(map[&K, &V] M) throws emptyMap
Description Returns an arbitrary key of map M.
Examples 
rascal>import Map;
ok
rascal>getOneFrom(("apple": 1, "pear": 2, "pineapple": 3));
str: "apple"
rascal>getOneFrom(("apple": 1, "pear": 2, "pineapple": 3));
str: "pineapple"
rascal>getOneFrom(("apple": 1, "pear": 2, "pineapple": 3));
str: "pineapple"
